  <statement>
      
                <p>Kurbika wants to have $1610 in a bank account that pays
                4.2% compounded annually after 15 years. 
                    <ol>
                      <li>How much money will should they invest today?</li>
                      <li>How much interest will they earn?</li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
      
      <p>

      </p>
      
  </statement>
    
  <answer>
      
              <p>
              <ol>
                <li>They need to invest <m>\frac{P_0}{(1 + \frac{r}{n})^{nt}} = \frac{1610}{(1 + \frac{0.042}{1})^{1\cdot 15}} = </m> $868.58 today.</li>
                <li><m>P_0 - FV = 1610 - 868.58 = </m> $741.42 in interest will be generated.</li>
              </ol>
            </p>
  </answer>
</exercise>
